Canada's leading composite indicatorrose 0.4 pct in January with eight of the 10 major componentsposting gains, the most widespread monthly advance in the pastyear, Statistics Canada said.    The index also gained 0.4 pct in the preceeding month. Theunfiltered index, however, fell 0.1 pct in January after rising1.0 pct in December.    The gain was led by the residential construction indexwhile the manufacturing groups continued to improve and thestock market index turned up, the federal agency reported. Reuter&#3;